        <updateDate>2020-05-28T17:30:48Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><strong>Promoting Integrity in Medicare Act of 2019 or the PIMA of </strong><b>2019</b></p> <p>This bill expands&nbsp;Medicare's prohibition on physician self-referrals (i.e., the Stark law) to include, with specified exceptions,&nbsp;certain advanced imaging, anatomic pathology, radiation therapy, and physical therapy services. Additionally, the bill establishes increased civil monetary penalties for violations of the self-referral prohibition with respect to those services.</p> <p>The Centers for Medicare &amp; Medicaid Services shall conduct a&nbsp;compliance review&nbsp;with respect to such referrals.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
